HEADWORD: Dequantitate
<hw>De*quan"ti*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>quantitas</ets>, <ets>-atis</ets>. See
<er>Quantity</er>.]</ety> <def>To diminish the quantity of; to
disquantity.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

